      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BROOKLYN DAN (1) has come from the back row to win his two starts this time in, the first of them coming at Listed level at Melton. His record at this distance stands at three from five and he is much better served by the ace draw. Should get every chance from there. SOHO CHARMER (4) has been very good from wider barriers in each of his three starts this time in, finishing second in the NSW Derby last start to follow a win in the heats. Building a strong record at this distance with two wins and a placing from three attempts. Could challenge. REWATCH (5) raced parked and couldn't finish off in a Derby heat last start but came from wider than this when winning first up at Menangle prior and he has yet to miss a place in four tries at this distance, winning twice. IM NO TROUBLE (6) has recorded four wins and a placing in five starts at this distance and won his only previous second-up attempt so could be an improver.",
